                "Happiness is Solving Problems: Life is a never-ending series of problems. True happiness is not the absence of problems; it is finding problems that you actually enjoy solving.",
                "Choose Your Struggle: Instead of asking 'What do I want out of life?', ask 'What pain do I want?'. Every success requires suffering. You must fall in love with the process and the pain associated with your goal.",
                "You Are Not Special: The modern obsession with being 'extraordinary' creates crippling anxiety. Accepting that you are mostly average takes the pressure off and allows you to enjoy simple, everyday life.",
                "The Value of Suffering: Growth only happens through pain and failure. Shielding yourself (or your children) from failure creates a fragile, entitled mindset. Embrace failure as a necessary stepping stone.",
